hydra [options] <target> <service> [service options]

Common Command Line Options
-l USER or -L FILE: Specify a single username or a list of usernames.
-p PASS or -P FILE: Specify a single password or a list of passwords.
-t TASKS: Number of parallel connections per target (default: 16).
-f / -F: Stop on the first valid username/password pair found.
-v / -V: Verbose mode. Shows the login/pass combinations being tried.
-w TIME: Set the delay between connection attempts in seconds.
-s PORT: Use a specific port instead of the default service port.
**-S`: Use SSL for the connection.
-R: Resume a previous, interrupted scan.
-o FILE: Write found credentials to a file.
-M FILE: Provide a list of target hosts for a parallel scan.
**-U`: List all available modules (protocols
